<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,479,835,894]" box="[151,430,870,894]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
(
<figureCitation box="[158,249,870,894]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="44.[151,229,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,172,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-88@44.[197,1396,159,1930]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="PLATE 4. A–I. General habitus. (A) Dialodia longilobata, sp. nov.; (B) Dialodia bispinata, sp. nov.; (C) Dialodia bilongata, sp. nov.; (D) Dialodia brevisetacea, sp. nov.; (E) Dialodia aviculobata, sp. nov.; (F) Evansolidia setacea, sp. nov.; (G) Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov.; (H) Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov.; (I) Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Plate 4I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[261,422,870,894]" captionStart="FIGURES 266–274" captionStartId="81.[151,257,1868,1889]" captionTargetBox="[217,1387,211,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-68@81.[189,1397,191,1846]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="FIGURES 266–274. Evansolidia lyrata, sp. nov. (266) male pygofer, lateral view; (267) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (268) right style, lateral view; (269) right style, dorsal view; (270) aedeagus, lateral view; (271) aedeagus, dorsal view; (272) dorsal connective, lateral view (273); dorsal connective, dorsal view; (274) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs. 266–274</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,942,1902]" box="[151,694,942,967]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,943,967]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 7.70–8.00 mm; female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,942,1902]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,979,1003]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Medium size, robust species. General color black and yellow. Forewings with yellow veins and cells on middle of clavus, cells translucent except on distal ¼; mesonotum with yellow marking basally and on each side of middle, yellow stripe on anterior half of lateral margins; pronotum with yellow broken band on anterior margin, irregular shaped yellow markings below anterior margin; crown yellow with black spot on each side of middle near anterior margin; eyes dark grey; face yellow with reddish brown longitudinal stripe on lateral margins of clypeus; clypellus with reddish brown bordered by black stripe on lateral margins, black stripe below eyes (
<figureCitation box="[217,310,1194,1218]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="44.[151,229,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,172,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-88@44.[197,1396,159,1930]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="PLATE 4. A–I. General habitus. (A) Dialodia longilobata, sp. nov.; (B) Dialodia bispinata, sp. nov.; (C) Dialodia bilongata, sp. nov.; (D) Dialodia brevisetacea, sp. nov.; (E) Dialodia aviculobata, sp. nov.; (F) Evansolidia setacea, sp. nov.; (G) Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov.; (H) Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov.; (I) Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Plate 4I</figureCitation>
). Head narrower than pronotum, anterior margin broadly rounded; crown broad, about as wide as width of eyes, produced distally about ¼ of entire length, lateral margins convergent basally, slightly carinate, disk depressed on each side of middle; eyes large, semiglobular; pronotum about as long as median length of crown, surface sparsely bullated; mesonotum large, nearly twice as long as median length of pronotum; forewings typical; clypeus long, narrow, lateral margins broadly convex; clypellus short, about 1/3 as long as clypeus, narrow, inflated baso-medially, lateral margins constricted medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,942,1902]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,376,1410,1435]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view broad, subtriangulate, small digital lobe and few setae on caudodorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[245,344,1446,1470]" captionStart="FIGURES 266–274" captionStartId="81.[151,257,1868,1889]" captionTargetBox="[217,1387,211,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-68@81.[189,1397,191,1846]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="FIGURES 266–274. Evansolidia lyrata, sp. nov. (266) male pygofer, lateral view; (267) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (268) right style, lateral view; (269) right style, dorsal view; (270) aedeagus, lateral view; (271) aedeagus, dorsal view; (272) dorsal connective, lateral view (273); dorsal connective, dorsal view; (274) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 266</figureCitation>
); subgenital plate long, narrow, few setae apically (
<figureCitation box="[921,1020,1446,1470]" captionStart="FIGURES 266–274" captionStartId="81.[151,257,1868,1889]" captionTargetBox="[217,1387,211,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-68@81.[189,1397,191,1846]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="FIGURES 266–274. Evansolidia lyrata, sp. nov. (266) male pygofer, lateral view; (267) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (268) right style, lateral view; (269) right style, dorsal view; (270) aedeagus, lateral view; (271) aedeagus, dorsal view; (272) dorsal connective, lateral view (273); dorsal connective, dorsal view; (274) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 267</figureCitation>
); style robust, shorter than aedeagus, in lateral view broadly expanded medially on lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[833,998,1482,1506]" captionStart="FIGURES 266–274" captionStartId="81.[151,257,1868,1889]" captionTargetBox="[217,1387,211,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-68@81.[189,1397,191,1846]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="FIGURES 266–274. Evansolidia lyrata, sp. nov. (266) male pygofer, lateral view; (267) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (268) right style, lateral view; (269) right style, dorsal view; (270) aedeagus, lateral view; (271) aedeagus, dorsal view; (272) dorsal connective, lateral view (273); dorsal connective, dorsal view; (274) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs. 268, 269</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long, tubular, with few subbasal spines and 1 subapically (
<figureCitation box="[502,667,1518,1542]" captionStart="FIGURES 266–274" captionStartId="81.[151,257,1868,1889]" captionTargetBox="[217,1387,211,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-68@81.[189,1397,191,1846]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="FIGURES 266–274. Evansolidia lyrata, sp. nov. (266) male pygofer, lateral view; (267) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (268) right style, lateral view; (269) right style, dorsal view; (270) aedeagus, lateral view; (271) aedeagus, dorsal view; (272) dorsal connective, lateral view (273); dorsal connective, dorsal view; (274) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs. 270, 271</figureCitation>
); connective broadly Y-shaped, membranous on each side of middle, stem broad, very short (
<figureCitation box="[417,515,1554,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 266–274" captionStartId="81.[151,257,1868,1889]" captionTargetBox="[217,1387,211,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-68@81.[189,1397,191,1846]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="FIGURES 266–274. Evansolidia lyrata, sp. nov. (266) male pygofer, lateral view; (267) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (268) right style, lateral view; (269) right style, dorsal view; (270) aedeagus, lateral view; (271) aedeagus, dorsal view; (272) dorsal connective, lateral view (273); dorsal connective, dorsal view; (274) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 272</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective long, narrow, base expanded in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1239,1336,1554,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 266–274" captionStartId="81.[151,257,1868,1889]" captionTargetBox="[217,1387,211,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-68@81.[189,1397,191,1846]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="FIGURES 266–274. Evansolidia lyrata, sp. nov. (266) male pygofer, lateral view; (267) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (268) right style, lateral view; (269) right style, dorsal view; (270) aedeagus, lateral view; (271) aedeagus, dorsal view; (272) dorsal connective, lateral view (273); dorsal connective, dorsal view; (274) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 273</figureCitation>
), sinuate in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[326,425,1590,1614]" captionStart="FIGURES 266–274" captionStartId="81.[151,257,1868,1889]" captionTargetBox="[217,1387,211,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-68@81.[189,1397,191,1846]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="FIGURES 266–274. Evansolidia lyrata, sp. nov. (266) male pygofer, lateral view; (267) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (268) right style, lateral view; (269) right style, dorsal view; (270) aedeagus, lateral view; (271) aedeagus, dorsal view; (272) dorsal connective, lateral view (273); dorsal connective, dorsal view; (274) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 274</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
