<subSubSection box="[199,1034,1806,1831]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,942,1902]" box="[199,1034,1806,1831]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1807,1831]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is descriptive for the many spines on the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,942,1902]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1843,1867]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has similar aedeagal features to 
<taxonomicName authority="Nielson, 2011" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="2011" box="[855,996,1843,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Evansolidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilitas" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[855,872,1843,1866]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[889,996,1843,1867]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">gracilitas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1012,1105,1843,1867]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1012,1105,1843,1867]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and can be separated by the much broader style, larger pygofer and longer pregenital plate and aedeagus.
</paragraph>
